text: Schuyler is a city in Colfax County, Nebraska, United States. As of the 2020 census, 6,547 people lived there. It is the county seat of Colfax County. The city and the county are named after Schuyler Colfax, former Vice President of the United States of America. == Geography == Schuyler is at (41.448916, âˆ’97.060195).
